---
const lastUpdated = 'June 18, 2026';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>Privacy Policy | PMP Recipes</title>
		<meta
			name="description"
				content="Privacy policy for PMP Recipes, including what is stored on your device, what we do not collect, and how we handle network requests."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<main class="policy-shell">
			<a class="back-link" href="/">← Back to home</a>
			<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
			<p class="updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

			<section>
				<h2>Summary</h2>
				<p>
						PMP Recipes is designed to help you browse and save recipes without building a user
						profile. The app does not use advertising SDKs, analytics SDKs, or background
						tracking.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
					<h2>What the app stores on your device</h2>
				<p>
						Some settings, saved recipes, or browsing state may be stored locally on your device so
						the app can remember your preferences and work offline where possible. This local data
						stays on your device unless you choose to remove it.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
					<h2>What we do not collect</h2>
				<p>
						We do not intentionally collect account information, contact lists, location data,
						ad identifiers, usage analytics, crash telemetry, payment details, or personal recipe
						preferences from your device.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
					<h2>Network activity</h2>
				<p>
						If the app requests recipe data, images, or related content from the internet, those
						requests are used only to load the content you asked to view. The app does not send your
						personal saved data as part of those requests.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
					<h2>Third-party services</h2>
					<p>
						PMP Recipes does not rely on third-party advertising networks or behavioral tracking
						services. If the app uses external libraries or hosted content, they are used only for
						basic app functionality.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Data sharing</h2>
					<p>
						We do not sell personal information. We do not share your local app data with data
						brokers, advertisers, or analytics providers.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
				<h2>Children's privacy</h2>
				<p>
						Because the app is not designed to collect personal data, it does not knowingly collect
						information from children.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
					<h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
					<p>
						If our privacy practices change in a meaningful way, this policy will be updated before
						the change is released.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
				<h2>Contact</h2>
				<p>
						If you have questions about this policy, please contact the app publisher through the
						support channel listed for the app.
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	:root {
		color-scheme: light;
		font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
		background: linear-gradient(180deg, #fffaf4 0%, #fff 100%);
		color: #221813;
	}

	body {
		margin: 0;
		min-height: 100vh;
	}

	.policy-shell {
		max-width: 760px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 2rem 1.25rem 3rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
	}

	.back-link {
		display: inline-block;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		color: #a4551d;
		text-decoration: none;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	h1,
	h2,
	p {
		margin-top: 0;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 6vw, 3.5rem);
		line-height: 1;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.updated {
		color: #6b5446;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	section + section {
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
	}

	h2 {
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
	}

	p {
		color: #4f4036;
	}
</style>
